Mass Exodus






I made a Widespread Panic a couple of years back featuring a mass exodus of flying turtles in search of a new home. The whale and birds in this print are likely a few days behind them. The flock of birds resemble a school of fish emphasizing a feeling of safety in numbers.  Also of note is the sharp printing on this one along with a noticeable textured under print that's only seen in person.
NOTES: 18 x 12 inches /// 5 screens (2 metallic) /// editions signed and numbered: silver to 50 copies (sold out) & blue whale to 200 copies /// debuted at SXSW Flatstock 2017





                Default Title - Sold Out
              













